Day 10: Metadata Analysis (EXIF)

Introduction

Welcome to Day 10 of my 30 Days of OSINT (Open Source Intelligence) Challenge.

Today, I explored Metadata Analysis (EXIF), an essential OSINT technique that helps investigators extract hidden information from digital files such as images, documents, videos, and PDFs.

At first glance, a file only shows its visible content. However, hidden inside it is metadata—information that can reveal details about when the file was created, which device was used, the software involved, timestamps, and in some cases, even the location where it was captured.

One of the biggest lessons from today's learning is that every digital file has a story beyond what we see. Metadata helps investigators uncover that story while using publicly available or authorized files in an ethical manner.


